ZAPIER.name: Zapier
ZAPIER.tagline: Automation platform—$5B valuation, $400M revenue, 8,000+ app integrations, bootstrapped
ZAPIER.overview: Zapier is an automation platform that connects 8,000+ apps to create custom workflows without coding. Founded in 2011 by Wade Foster and Bryan Helmig, the company is remarkably capital-efficient—reaching $5B valuation on just $2.68M in VC funding ($1.4M from Sequoia/YC). Revenue grew to $400M projected for 2025, up from $310M in 2024. The company has 3M+ users and 100K+ paying customers. In September 2025, Zapier launched unified AI orchestration plans with Tables, Interfaces, and Zapier MCP. The company remains remote-first with no physical headquarters.
